@startuml Merge_Flow_Activity
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #1E1E2E
skinparam defaultFontColor #CDD6F4
skinparam activityBorderColor #585B70
skinparam arrowColor #89B4FA

title MIDAS — Merge Flow (Activity Diagram)

|#1E1E2E|Hub|
start

:Initial state:\n- Slot 1: primary base (typified)\n- Slot 2: empty;

:User clicks "Load second base";

|#1E1E2E|Loading|
:Open FileDialog\n(.csv or .arff);

:User selects file;

if (Valid file?) then (no)
  :Show error dialog;
  stop
else (yes)
endif

:Load file via controller\n(CSVController or ARFFController);

if (Format?) then (CSV)
  :Show delimiter dialog;
  :Load via loadCsv();
  :Auto-typify attributes\n(infer_types_from_df);
  note right
    Infers ARFF-style types:
    Numeric, Textual, Nominal, Date
  end note
else (ARFF)
  :Load via loadArff();
  :Keep types from @ATTRIBUTE;
endif

:Sync with StateManager\n(syncFromCSV / syncFromARFF);
:Mark as preprocessed;

|#1E1E2E|Hub|
:Return to **page_hub**;

:Updated state:\n- Slot 1: primary base\n- Slot 2: secondary base\n- Merge action: ENABLED (if both typified);

:User selects both slots\nthen clicks "Merge" card;

|#1E1E2E|Step 1: Map Columns|
:Show **page_merge** — Step 1;

:User defines column mappings;
note right
  Map columns that represent
  the same data across bases.
  e.g. "customer_id" ↔ "id"

  Type compatibility is validated:
  Numeric↔Numeric ✓
  Textual↔Nominal ✓
  Numeric↔Textual ✗
end note

:Click "Next";

|#1E1E2E|Step 2: Configure Merge|

if (Has mappings?) then (yes)
  :Show all JOIN options;
  note right
    - inner join
    - left join
    - right join
    - cross join
  end note
  :Select key column\n(from mapped columns dropdown);
else (no)
  :Only cross join available;
  note right: Cartesian product
endif

:Click "Update preview";
:View sample of merged result;

if (Result satisfactory?) then (no)
  :Adjust settings;
  backward:Redo preview;
else (yes)
endif

:Click "Execute merge";

|#1E1E2E|Execution|
:MergeService.execute();
:pandas.merge() with parameters;

if (Merge succeeded?) then (yes)
  :Result → replaces primary;
  :Secondary cleared;
  :Merged types = union of both\nselected_types dicts;
  :Show **success popup**\n(row & column counts);
else (no)
  :Show error dialog;
  |#1E1E2E|Step 2: Configure Merge|
  :Return to settings;
  stop
endif

|#1E1E2E|Post-Merge|

if (User chooses?) then (Export)
  :Open FileDialog\n(ARFF / CSV);
  :SerializationService.save();
  :clearAllBases();
else (Return without saving)
  :clearAllBases();
endif

|#1E1E2E|Hub|
:Replace stack with **page_hub**;

:Final state:\n- Slot 1: empty\n- Slot 2: empty\n- Ready for new session;

stop

@enduml
